import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(group_counts.index, group_counts.values)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of groups in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    chart = group_counts.plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, 
                              colors=['#ff9999','#66b3ff','#99ff99'], 
                              wedgeprops={'linewidth': 2, 'edgecolor': 'white'})
    plt.title('What is the most common group in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count()
    person_counts = data.groupby('person')['group'].count()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(group_counts.index, group_counts.values, label='Group')
    ax.bar(person_counts.index, person_counts.values, label='Person')
    ax.set_xlabel('Group/Person')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of people in each group?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    unique_persons = data.groupby('group')['person'].nunique().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.barh(unique_persons.index, unique_persons.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Unique Person Count')
    ax.set_ylabel('Group')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of unique people in each group?')
    for i, v in enumerate(unique_persons.values):
        ax.text(v + 0.5, i - 0.1, str(v), color='blue', fontweight='bold')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['group'], data['person'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between group and person?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
